New Records: Gunnar Henderson tied the Orioles' single-season home run record for a shortstop with his 34th home run, matching Cal Ripken Jr. and Miguel Tejada.
Key Match Events: Gunnar Henderson hit a home run in his first at-bat, ending a weeklong drought and scoring the Orioles' first run.
The Orioles won the game 13-3 against the White Sox.
Cedric Mullins hit a two-run homer in the bottom of the eighth inning.
Each Orioles starter recorded a hit and scored a run for the first time since August 25, 2017.
Post-Match Reflections: Gunnar Henderson expressed pride in tying the home run record and emphasized focusing on helping the team win.
Manager Brandon Hyde praised Henderson's performance and the team's ability to regain momentum.
Starter Corbin Burnes highlighted the team's offensive potential and hoped the game would spark continued success.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles' 12th leadoff home run of the season tied the franchise record set in 1996 and leads MLB this year.
